column6: Volunteer Search & Rescue Team on call 24 hours a day 365 days a year. Trained in search, rope rescue, water rescue and first aid.
column31: *CALL OUTS* 25 - 28. 30/05/20 An afternoon none of our team will forget in a hurry. The pagers sounded at 15:50, Solent asked the team to assist South Western Ambulance Service NHS Foundation Trust with a casulty who had been pulled from the sea bed after jumping from Durdle Door. Also tasked were Lulworth First Responders Kimmeridge Coastguard, Weymouth Lifeboat, Dorset Police, Dorset and Somerset Air Ambulance and Coastguard Rescue 175. Arriving on scene, the team made their way down the steps to the beach, locating the casualty near to the base of the steps. He was receiving help from the medical professionals already on scene. Lulworth CRT began to create a landing site for the helicopter. The beach had thousands of people on it and we thank the majority of people who complied with our shouting to clear a helicopter landing site, a very difficult challenge. Helimed landed on the beach. We were then made aware of a second casualty 2/3 of the way around the beach who had also jumped from the door. Somehow he had managed stagger back to his friends before falling very unwell. The paramedics deemed his injuries very serious and requested that like the first casualty, he be flown to the major trauma centre in Southampton. Team members and police now had to clear a second landing site for Rescue 175 which had been circling the area. The beach was cleared, many day trippers now on Scratchy Bottom beach. The second helicopter landed, unloaded their paramedic and stretcher before returning to base to refuel. The second casualty was carefully prepared for hospital. The first helicopter then left scene, flying at best speed to Southampton. The police then declared the beach to be closed. The thousands caught in-between the two landing sites now asked to leave the beach. Our Senior Coastal Operations Officer had been maintaining communications on high ground when a third casualty made himself known to him. He had also jumped from Durdle Door and had serious injuries to his torso. An ambulance crew (one of five on site) dealt with his injuries and took him to Dorset County Hospital on Dorchester. Rescue 175 was now back on scene and landed again on the beach. The second casualty was loaded on board, and flown to Southampton. They were met by our colleagues at Hill Head Coastguard Rescue Team who assisted with the transfers. The remaining beach goers were now asked to leave. The police had to deal with alcohol fuelled minor scuffles, as well as a small but out of control fire from a BBQ. On returning up the steps, a fourth casualty had identified on high ground above Durdle Door. The lady had a suspected broken ankle and due to gradient of the hill, a stretcher carry out was too risky. Coastgaurd Rescue 187 from St Athan was sent to the area. They dropped their paramedics on top of the hill, and walked down to the lady. She was placed in a rescue strop and winched into the aircraft. They flew her to the top of the hill and transferred her to a land ambulance. After a debrief, Lulworth and Kimmeridge retuned to their stations at about 21:30. We understand that four individuals jumped from Durdle Door (some 70ft) yesterday, encouraged by the crowds on the beach. Two of which are now seriously injured. Upsetting scenes like we and many others witnessed yesterday illustrate how very dangerous tombstoning is. We couldn‚Äôt discourage it enough. Thank you everyone who helped in one way or another yesterday including the Lulworth Estate staff who, as usual, were integral to keeping traffic flowing aiding emergency vehicles entering the area. We wish all the casualties the very best. We would also like to reiterate our thanks to the vast majority of beach goers who were patient and cooperative in what was very difficult situation. Described as a critical incident by police.

column31: PLEASE SHARE - HOW YOU CAN HELP THE WILDLIFE IN THE BUSHFIRE & EVAC The Animal Rescue Collective (ARC) and The Rescue Collective have for months now been running emergency response for Wildlife and Animals caught up in the fires. We have shipped over 80 tonne of food, hundreds of packages of medicine, blankets, supportive garments and water storage. This is the largest animal rescue support project in Australian History, getting product and support to hundreds of Animal Resccuers, field workers and volunteers everywhere. Drop zones all the way from QLD to Tasmania. HERE IS HOW YOU CAN BE INVOLVED Donate financially here, this is a registered Animal Rescue charity https://mkc.org.au/donations/trcqld THIS FAQ TELLS YOU HOW YOU CAN HELP - Wishlist items we will need - How do donate money - How to volunteer as a transporter - How to volunteer as a safehouse, drop hub - How to volunteer as a field worker BUT this is only for people in the firezones who can be on the ground - How to volunteer as a craft maker and join the craft guild (EG, this means sewing, kitting, making supportive garments etc) - How to volunteer as a maker of hard product Anything else please comment BUT please understand we are absolutely flat out and we may not reply immediately. JOIN THE CHAT GROUPS National https://www.facebook.com/groups/mkcfreecycle https://www.facebook.com/therescuecollective WISHLIST ITEMS YOU CAN FIND THAT WE WILL NEED If you want to send product to us, here is the wishlist of items we need (Thanks Nicole) WISHLIST HAY AND CHAFF - oaten, meadow, teff ‚≠êÔ∏èMACROPOD PELLETS OR MITAVITE ECONOMIX ‚≠êÔ∏èHANGING BASKETS/PLANTERS - Wire with coir ‚≠êÔ∏èBLANKETS - E.g. Kmart pet blankets ‚≠êÔ∏èPET BOWLS üå±BAXTER FLUIDS (point 9) üê®BIOLAC FORMULAS üå±LECTADE ORAL HYDRATION üå±VETAFARM SPARK FLUIDS üê®WOMBAROO IMPACT üå±FUEL CARDS üê®F10 VETERINARY DISINFECTANT üå±METACAM, MOLOXICOM üå±SYRINGES 1-60ML (cheap on ebay) üê®VETAFARM CRITTA CARE üå±ANIMAL WOUND GELS & SPRAYS üê®NUTRIGEL üê®ANIMAL FEEDING BOTTLES & TEATS üå±VETWRAP (everyone needs vetwrap) ‚≠êÔ∏èDomestic animal foo ‚≠êÔ∏èSOFFBAN (Lots needed) ‚≠êÔ∏èChlorsig ‚≠êÔ∏èIV Fluid infusion sets and canulars ‚≠êÔ∏èCoffee ‚≠êÔ∏èMicro Pourous Tape ‚≠êÔ∏èNon adhesive dressings (like melonin) ‚≠êÔ∏èPLASTIC BASINS ‚≠êÔ∏èSANDPITS ‚≠êÔ∏èJERRY CANS FOR WATER ‚≠êÔ∏è10L CASKS OF WATER ‚≠êÔ∏è*NEW* LITTER TRAYS (to use as water basins for smaller animals) You can order products or vouchers online from various pet & vet store. VOLUNTEER TO FEED ANIMALS IN THE FIREZONES Please complete this if you are able to drive to the places where help is needed and work with the local rescue teams. https://rescuedpets.com.au/macrofooddrops/ REQUEST HELP FOR YOUR ORG Please complete this if you are actually feeding or helping animals. https://rescuedpets.com.au/support/ NOMINATE AS A DROP OFF HUB OR SAFEHOUSE https://rescuedpets.com.au/add-listing/ NOMINATE AS A TRANSPORTER (UTES/VANS/TRUCKS NEEDED, not small cars) https://rescuedpets.com.au/transporter/ JOIN THE CRAFT GUILD TO MAKE THINGS THAT HELP https://www.facebook.com/groups/arfsncrafts/ JOIN THE MAKERS GUILD TO BUILD POSSUM BOXES AND HARD TO CUSTOMISE FEED/WATER ITEMS https://www.facebook.com/groups/arcmakers/ Anything else please comment below but please know what you can offer and how you can help! All volunteers getting supplies and support everywhere we can.

column31: In a new issue brief, MI‚Äôs James Copland weighs in on the nationwide debate over critical race theory, suggesting how voters and policymakers can curb racially charged pedagogy in their local schools. Copland‚Äôs guidance is grounded in constitutional principles and follows in the footsteps of states like Arizona and Idaho that have aimed to curtail racialized instruction and compelled speech through democratically supported legislation. When passing related legislation, policymakers SHOULD strive to provide parents greater visibility over school curricula and training and ensure the prohibition of government-compelled speech. Legislatures SHOULD NOT try to stifle the marketplace of ideas, proscribe or discourage classroom discussion of race and racism, or undermine educational pluralism in non-district schools, among other concerns. column31: Open Letter from Spirit Voyage's CEO, Karan Khalsa, to the Collaborative Response Team of the Siri Singh Sahib Corporation Sent March 2, 2020 Sat Nam, I am writing to you as the team tasked with navigating the difficult process of reaching the truth of the sexual allegations that have been made about Yogi Bhajan. I am deeply grateful that the organizations who have been stewards of Yogi Bhajan‚Äôs teachings have taken the brave step of creating this team and pursuing an independent investigation. In the last 2 weeks, I have personally heard from 7 women whose stories of being abused by Yogi Bhajan have been heartbreaking. They are horrifying. Having been raised in this Kundalini Yoga community, many of the women who have come forward are my childhood friends. I believe most of them would never have shared their stories in order to protect those they loved. Pamela‚Äôs book started this, but this is not about her story alone. More women are now rising up to support truth by sharing their stories. Truth is truth and can be uncovered no matter how much time has passed. You all know me. You know that Yogi Bhajan was like a grandfather to me. In my life, he gave me so much kindness, direction, discipline and love. He visited my room during my first 40 days of life. He officiated at my wedding. He supported me in my divorce. He held my family in his protective shield through so many challenges. I come to you as someone who has always loved him with a pure and open heart. As a child of this community and these teachings, I was raised to believe that we are here to protect each other, to protect those that cannot protect themselves. You are now being asked to step up and help provide protection to women from our own family who have come forward with stories of serious sexual abuse. I pray you are up for that task. Yogi Bhajan passed away almost 16 years ago. Since well before that time, yogis around the world have made Kundalini Yoga‚Äôs teachings their own, have been healed by them, have been transformed by them, have begun teaching them and sharing the incredible medicine that they contain. Kundalini Yoga is medicine to me. Kundalini Yoga‚Äôs music is what has made me believe in the Divine within myself. The Kundalini Yoga community is my family. These last few weeks, as I heard the stories of women who were abused, I questioned everything I was raised to believe including my practice of Kundalini Yoga. I reached out to a dear friend of mine. She said, ‚ÄúKaran, I didn‚Äôt start doing Kundalini Yoga because of Yogi Bhajan. I‚Äôm certainly not going to stop because of him.‚Äù That simple statement gave me comfort and gave me permission to keep practicing. I believe these teachings will fulfill their destiny of transcending any teacher. We are all part of its creation story. Our experiences are what make it real. We are all its teachers now. As you know, I am not only a student of Kundalini Yoga, I also own multiple businesses that share its teachings. I have been so proud to be a woman-owned and woman-run business sharing Kundalini Yoga. After learning of these allegations, I can no longer connect to Yogi Bhajan when I practice. I will no longer be responsible for sharing his name and likeness with the world. Yogi Bhajan may have been the vessel that carried these teachings to the west, but I believe it is time for me to remove him from the Kundalini Yoga shared at Spirit Voyage, Sat Nam Fest and Kundalini Yoga U. My team and I are embarking on the task of removing him from our various websites and social media. It is both an emotional clearing and a statement of sovereignty from him. People have warned me that I may be destroying my business by doing this. I am willing to take that risk. Kundalini Yoga is a practice of yoga that belongs to all of us. It is not an individual. I believe this is part of its real lesson to all of us. I know that you and the organizations you represent must wait for the outcome of the investigation to take your next steps. There is so much at stake right now for our community. The world is watching us. Tens of thousands of people are engaged in daily conversations about these allegations. If you are not members of the online forums, you might not know how far-reaching the impact of these allegations goes. If we as a community can show the world that we are ready and willing to openly acknowledge these allegations and enter into a process to restore truth and justice, only then will our community survive. My request to you is that you will ensure that no abuse, sexual or otherwise, is tolerated in our community. I am asking you, as the CRT, to ensure the following in this investigation and in the future: - You will make it very easy for people to report abuse. - Where abuse occurs, you will stop it and a full investigation will be completed. - The results of the investigation will be open and transparent. - Reparations and healing including therapy and counseling to victims (truncated)

column34: ***Priority Medical Placement Needed for TOMMY Needs 24Hr Hospital for Supportive Care and Monitoring** TOMMY 116911 Female, 5 Years Old FIV+ Severe URI conjunctivitis Emaciated. Elevated ALT
column36:
***Pulled by Little Wanderers NYC***

***Priority Medical Placement Needed for TOMMY - Needs 24Hr Hospital for Supportive Care and Monitoring***

ACC NYC ‚Äì Brooklyn Center

A staff member writes: Tommy needs to go to a 24hr Hospital for continued monitoring and supportive care. She a severe URI and has a possible abscess in her eye w/ conjunctivitis and wounds around the eyes, likely self-inflicted; she is FIV positive and is dehydrated, emaciated, and has dental disease. Tommy‚Äôs ALT levels are elevated and has severe leukocytosis - likely infection/inflammation. She has alopecia that might be ringworm ‚Äì the woods lamp fluoresced a few hairs around the alopecia. She has been calm and tolerant of handling, but squirms and tries to flee during treatments.

TOMMY 116911

5 Years ‚Äì Female ‚Äì 4lbs ‚Äì Stray

15-May-2021

Hx: 5/14/2021 Stray intake-URI, conjunctivitis, wounds, FIV+, elevated ALT, leukocytosis, emaciated, dental disease, alopecia, and dehydration. IVC placed and started bolus. Started on cerenia, clavamox, simbadol, gentamycin, and nebulization. Given famotidine once.

CBC: severe leukocytosis 46.59 (2.87-17.02); severe neutrophilia 32.51 (2.30-10.29) with suspected bands and toxic neutrophils; lymphocytosis 12.15 (0.92-6.88); monocytosis 1.72 (0.05-0.67); eosinopenia 0.12 (0.17-1.57); thrombocytopenia 39 (151-600) with plt aggregates detected
CHEM: mild ADMA elevation 15 (0-14); creat wnl 1.1 (0.8-2.4); mild BUN elevation 39 (16-36); mild hyperphosphatemia 8.2 (3.1-7.5); mild hypokalemia 3.3 (3.5-5.8); hyperglobulinemia 5.9 (2.8-5.1); moderate ALT elevation 469 (12-130); low ALP <10 (14-111)
T4: wnl

Today, 5/15-Progress exam, overall recheck

SO: QAR ~6-7% dehydrated, no c/v/d, sneezing. Unremarkable elimination, initially very tolerant of handling but attempting to flee during end of PE and treatments. Easily toweled and allowed all handling.

T = 100.8F
P = WNL
R = WNL
BCS = 2/9

EENT: OU crusted shut, severe mucopurulent-hemorrhagic discharge expressed from OU, able to visualize globe!!! OD skin at medial canthi has two full thickness wounds, each <0.5cm; OU globe unremarkable, mild-mod conjunctival hyperemia noted OU. OS has severe chemosis, pinpoint wound at medial canthi has mild-mod purulent to hemorrhagic discharge. Moderate mucoid nasal discharge. AU mild ceruminous debris with no evidence of otitis externa.
Oral Exam: adult dentition, moderate dental plaque/tartar, mild-mod gingival inflammation, no oral lesions. MM pink, moist, CRT <2s. Prolonged skin tent appreciated
PLN: No enlargements noted
H/L: No murmurs or arrhythmias ausculted. AU increased BV sounds with marked congestion, increased/harsh RUAS
ABD: Soft, non-painful, no masses palpated, doughy on palpation
U/G: FI, no MGT, no discharge
MSI: Ambulatory x 4, skin free of parasites, no masses noted, dirty/dull/unkempt hair coat, marked generalized muscle wasting, focal spot of alopecia with short hairs caudal to AD, thinning of fur on ventrum
CNS: Mentation appropriate - no signs of neurologic abnormalities
Rectal: Not performed, externally normal

A:
URI
Conjunctivitis with mucopurulent/hemorrhagic discharge - ro infectious conjunctivitis vs discharge/inflammation secondary to wounds
Wounds at medial canthi OU - ro self trauma vs other
FIV+
Elevated ALT
Severe leukocytosis - likely infection/inflammation
Emaciation
Dehydration
Dental disease
Alopecia - ro RW vs overgrooming/scratching

Prog:
Guarded

P:
CTM while at BACC
Cleaned/flushed OU and wounds at medial canthi with saline.
Vitamin B12 0.4ml SQ once
Start mirtazapine on pinna SID x 4 days until 5/18-first dose given
Continue IV LRS @ 8 ml/hr
Continue cerenia 1 mg/kg SQ SID x 4 days until 5/17
Start Famotidine 1 mg/kg SQ BID x 4 days until 5/18-first dose given
Continue Clavamox 13.75 mg/kg PO BID x 7 days until 5/21
Continue Simbadol 0.24 mg/kg SQ SID x 4 days until 5/17
Continue nebulization w saline BID x 4 days until 5/18
Continue gentamycin OU BID x 10 days unitl 5/23
Monitor overall condition and appetite closely on daily rounds will need continued follow up/supportive care with RDVM for URI, wounds, and dehydration.
 
14-May-2021
Temp @ 6:30 pm - 99.2

Vet Notes: 4:45 PM
DVM Intake Exam

History : Stray, emergency
Estimated age: Approx 5-7 years
Microchip noted on Intake? Negative

Subjective: QAR to dull, allows most handling, squirms and resists some medical tasks
Evidence of Cruelty seen - none
Evidence of Trauma seen - none

Objective:
T = 96.6
P = wnl
R = wnl with inc inspiratory effort
BCS = 2/9

Upon cleaning - OD skin at medial canthi has two full thickness wounds, each <0.5cm; globe unremarkable, mild conjunctival hyperemia noted. column31: People constantly ask me, ‚ÄúWhat can I do?‚Äù You can start by celebrating Thanksgiving and Christmas however you want in defiance of irrational government edicts To say that we are passing through a period that is unique to the American experience is a bit of an understatement. I am not referring to the pandemic. That is not unique to this country or, for that matter, any other. I am referring to a seismic shift in how Americans view their government and how their government views them. While a graduate student in history, it was my great good fortune that famed historian Forrest McDonald, then in the autumn of his life, selected me to be one of his students. Such was his reputation by that time that the university let him do whatever he wanted, and for McDonald that meant writing and teaching only a handful of grad students of his own choosing. A conservative constitutional historian of considerable eminence, he made a habit, as the NYT put it, of ‚Äúpuncturing liberal notions.‚Äù Most of those notions dealt with the Left‚Äôs understanding‚Äîno, that is too generous: their deliberate mischaracterization‚Äîof the Constitution. With exacting historical accuracy, McDonald argued in multiple books that the Constitution was not intended to ‚Äúgrant freedoms.‚Äù That, the Framers believed, was not within the scope of government. Those rights were, in the words of the Declaration of Independence, ‚Äúinalienable‚Äù‚Äîthat is, they are ‚Äúnatural,‚Äù as Locke had put it, or, as the Declaration itself puts it, they are given by the Creator. Rather, the purpose of the Constitution was to restrain government by defining its boundaries in order to prevent it from infringing upon those inalienable rights. McDonald relentlessly celebrated America‚Äôs uniqueness, yes, its exceptionalism, among nations that oscillated between anarchy and oppression without finding the golden mean. In his seminal work E Pluribus Unum, he wrote: ‚ÄúThe French, the Russians, the Italians, the Germans, all the planet‚Äôs peoples in their turn, would become so unrestrained as to lose contact with sanity. The Americans might have suffered a similar history, had they followed the lead of those who, in 1787 and 1788, spoke in the name of the people and of popular ‚Äòrights.‚Äô But there were giants in the earth in those days, and they spoke in the name of the nation, and the people followed them. As a result, the Americans were, despite themselves, doomed forever to be free.‚Äù Were my old mentor alive today, I might quibble with a singular word in the last clause: forever. Today, American freedom is imperiled not simply because of the massive government overreach to which we are all being subjected, but by the ignorance of the American people themselves. Hosea 4:6 says, ‚ÄúMy people were destroyed from lack of knowledge.‚Äù We may add Americans to that text. The Lord commanded the Israelites to commemorate their history, to tell the stories of their national heroes to their children and of their deliverance, and to reflect upon all that the Lord had done for them. A nation dies when its history, its mythology, its symbols are no longer passed from one generation to the next. We now have multiple generations of Americans who have been inculcated with ideas that are antithetical to the principles‚Äîlargely Judeo-Christian principles, mind you‚Äîupon which this great nation was founded, and if they are not opposed, they will destroy all that was bequeathed to us. The great Russian historian Richard Pipes argued that the so-called ‚ÄúRussian Revolution‚Äù is a historical fiction. A revolution is, by definition, a popular rebellion, and that is not what happened in 1917 Russia. That idea is a bit of Bolshevik propaganda magic. Instead, says Pipes, it was a coup d‚Äô√©tat. That is, a seizure of power by a relatively small group of determined militants. This, I believe, is what we are witnessing. Whether you believe the presidential election was stolen or not, you‚Äôd have to be a fool if you don‚Äôt think radical elements within the Democrat Party will do anything‚Äîabsolutely anything‚Äîto gain power and enact a radical and utterly godless agenda. It is the nature of governments to test boundaries the way a thief tests door handles: if they are unlocked, the thief will go in. Right now, we are seeing cities and states controlled by Democrats testing any number of door handles, and, finding little or no resistance, they have been emboldened to swing the door wide and make themselves at home. Democrats now embrace censorship, intimidation tactics, Critical Race Theory, Marxism, and post-inauguration purges. The militia elements of their party, Antifa and Black Lives Matter, act with impunity in our streets the way Hitler‚Äôs notorious ‚ÄúBrown Shirts‚Äù once did on behalf of party interests. In a manner consistent with a socialist mentality that views mankind as just so much raw material for the building of the utopian state, the lives of decent, hardworking Americans are being destroyed by policies that (truncated)

Kinilala ang suspek na si Webster Rosales Simon, residente ng nabanggit na barangay. Ayon sa Albay Police Provincial Office, pasado alas onse ng tanghali nitong biernes (mayo-21) ng ikasa ng pinag isang pwersa ng Camarines Norte Provincial Cybercrime Response Team (PCRT), Camarines Sur PCRT at Naga CIty CRT ang isang entrapment operation laban kay Simon. Ito'y matapos na dumulog sa himpilan ng PNP ang 28 taong gulang na guro mula sa bayan ng Libmanan na kinikikilan umano ito ng pera kapalit ng hindi pagpapakalat sa mga malalaswa nitong litrato at video. Walang kaalam-alam si Simon na pulis na pala ang nagpadala ng pera na kanyang tinanggap sa isang money remittance center sa barangay Matacon. Kaagad na inaresto ng mga otoridad ang suspek kung saan nabawi sa kanya ang pera na tinanggap nito. Mahaharap ang suspek sa kasong paglabag sa RA 10175 o Cybercrime Prevention Act at kasong paglabag sa RA 9995 o Anti Photo and Video Voyeurism Act. Kasalukuyan ng hawak ng mga otoridad ang suspek para sa kaukulang disposisyon.///

column31: IT'S THURSDAY! TODAY'S FEATURED MEMBER OF OUR TEAM Roscio Giron, our #CRT was born and raised in Guatemala City. She comes from a big family, one constant in her family was that they each knew they wanted to do something substantial in their life. She started and completed her educational career in Guatemala from primary school to receiving her high school diploma, did a major in computer studies and minor in tourism and went on to complete her Respiratory Therapy program at the San Carlos University of Guatemala. But..Respiratory Therapy wasn't her first choice, this is a snippet of her story. While researching Rocio decided she wanted to become a nurse, she was registered and because she was academically inclined and had done most of her perquisite studies - it was a natural progression for her to get into nursing. At the last week before graduating nursing school, she felt she wanted to do more. In again researching of how to move forward, she had seen a traumatic experience where someone was having difficulty breathing and she felt helpless with not being able to help and her calling to become a respiratory therapist grew from just a thought to a reality. Having a base in nursery and medical field - it then came naturally to her when she started to immerse herself into Respiratory Therapy. Before ending this program she had already been offered a position as the CRT by a prestigious hospital in Guatemala, UNICAR. While being at UNICAR is where she met her mentors and senior RT's and this is where Rocio believes she learned most of her skills. She was challenged clinically in ways that the lessons learnt in theory and at school couldn't compare to what she went through in reality. She graduated from San Carlos in 2003 and at her work site is where she heard about Belize! In 2005 she heard that another private hospital in Belize was looking for a certified respiratory therapist because there were 2 in the country at the time but one had to leave. She was recommended as the RT, she then came and in a matter of three weeks she moved to Belize. She managed the ICU under an intensivist and another RT for 6 years. Rocio has practiced in most medical facilities in Belize and now 15 years after she came to this country she is not only a private practice CRT but she is also now Belizean and a mother of 2 Belizean boys! She is proud to be a part of this team here with Dr. Gabourel and everyone else as she has great professional chemistry with the doctors, nurses and staff. Rocio recounts that her pride stems from seeing this clinic as a Gastro and Endoscopy Center to what it is today, she has grown and expanded as much as the clinic has and its holistic approach to each and every patient. Rocio as our #CRT diagnoses, treats and manages all respiratory problems from Asthma to Sleep Apnea to Trauma. Rocio's biggest accomplishment is giving her patients the ability to breathe well again. Thanks for reading! You can like her page here https://www.facebook.com/rociogiron.crt/:=:https://www.facebook.com/login/?next=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Frociogiron.crt%2F

The name ‚ÄúTara Reade‚Äù would be uttered in every news segment. His touchiness toward girls would be the cause of feminist protests. His inability to finish a thought would be disqualifying. His eulogy for a former KKK member would be playing on loop. His proven lies & plagiarism over his 47 year political career would be detailed in full. We wouldn‚Äôt be talking about anything but Hunter Biden, and whether or not Joe‚Äôs foreign policy with nations like China can be bought. He‚Äôd be asked why he & the Obama admin put ‚Äúkids in cages‚Äù at the border & deported an unprecedented number of illegal immigrants. Instead, very few journalists are talking about these things, & Twitter is actively shutting down conversation about some of them. None of these these issues‚Äîall significant‚Äîare even known by many voting for Joe, & that‚Äôs exactly how they want it. I have no problem with journalists scrutinizing Trump. Most ‚Äújournalists‚Äù are left-wing ideologues & mere extensions of Democratic campaigns. And, if we had a press that was even 20% non-partisan, we‚Äôd hear about the other concerns at least half the country have: Does Joe Biden support late term abortion? Why does Joe support repealing the Hyde Amendment? What cases will be overturned if Dems pack the court? Does Joe support the Equality Act, which exists as a deliberate infringement upon religious liberty? Why didn‚Äôt Joe fight ‚Äúsystemic racism‚Äù during his 47 year political career + time as VP? Does Joe support critical race theory training subsidized by the taxpayer? Does he see China as the threat they are? Does he support protection of the 1st & 2nd amendments? How will he pay for his education + climate plans w/o raising taxes on those making less than $400K? Does Kamala still believe Joe is a racist who flirted with segregationists? Instead, we mostly get ‚ÄúJoe & Kamala are going to bring us together.‚Äù How? Like Obama did?
